<item>
            <title>[BATCH-1888] Add a job scope (like the step scope)</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/BATCH-1888</link>
                <project id="10090" key="BATCH">Spring Batch</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I think it&apos;s very usefull to add a &quot;Job&quot; scope to spring batch, like the &quot;Step&quot; scope.&lt;br/&gt;
I have a usecase where i use a dataholder bean to share data between differents steps of a given job. For thread-safety requirements, it will be very usefull to create a dataholder bean per every job execution.&lt;br/&gt;
PS: I don&apos;t want to store my dataholder bean on the job context, because it&apos;s voluminous and it will impact the performance of my job (I know that i should handle the serialization/deserialization of the bean in case of an execution failure of my job).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks in advance.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
